# Logout / Session Cleanup

To completely destroy a session (e.g., on logout), you need to:

1. Unset all session variables (`$_SESSION = []`).
2. Delete the session cookie if used.
3. Destroy the session data on the server with `session_destroy()`.

```php
session_start();
$_SESSION = []; // clear all session data

if (ini_get("session.use_cookies")) {
    $params = session_get_cookie_params();
    setcookie(session_name(), '', time() - 42000,
        $params["path"], $params["domain"],
        $params["secure"], $params["httponly"]
    );
}

session_destroy();
```

```php
<?php
session_start();

// Remove specific variable
unset($_SESSION['username']);

// Or clear all
$_SESSION = [];

// Destroy the session file
session_destroy();

// Redirect to login page
header('Location: login.php');
exit;
?>
```
